<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 5:56PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Alamance,
Moore, northwestern Scotland, southeastern Anson, eastern Montgomery,
Richmond, eastern Randolph and western Chatham Counties through 645
PM EDT...
At 556 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Asheboro to 13 miles south of Biscoe to
near Cheraw Municipal Airport. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Southern Pines, Rockingham, Carthage, Siler City, North
Carolina Zoo, Pinehurst, Hamlet, Aberdeen and Biscoe.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
